{"author":{"id":"68dfa65ee618df2786e7da658bbfbbcc1f0c757170d9426e314e5f0886bcc55d"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1704977618,"nonce":"FGojLFOYHAS4qI43KxmWCY8I9QI=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s57xfWi","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/5709","origin":"github"},"title":"Update emboss tools","message":"I just discovered that the emboss tools have a binary that generates Galaxy tool wrappers (and it seems that the original ones have been generated this way .. but this was never documented or it got lost)\n\nTools could be generated like this:\n\n```\nfor tool_name in emboss_*xml\ndo\n    basename=$(echo $tool_name | sed 's/emboss_//; s/\\.xml//');\n    acdgalaxy $basename | \n        sed 's/\\(\u003ctool .*\\)version=\"[^\"]\\+\"/\\1version=\"@TOOL_VERSION@+galaxy@VERSION_SUFFIX@\"/' |\n        sed 's/\\(\u003crequirement .*\\)version=\"[^\"]\\+\"/\\1version=\"@TOOL_VERSION@\"/' \n\ndone\n```\n\ntest that we have now could be handled with macros. But we would loose the quotes (`'`)? Maybe we can patch the emboss sources ... \n\nWondering how we could treat the versioning such that we do not break tool lineage (unfortunately the tool ids have spaces and mixed case letters and contain old version numbers).","files":null}]}